          <p corresp='TTP32579413P0' xml:id='OTP32579413P0'>[seal]
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32579413P1' xml:id='OTP32579413P1'><rs ref='#S95870'>Hd Qrs— Post</rs> of <rs ref='#S51727'>Port Gibson</rs>.<lb/>
Port Gibson Miss Aug 10 1865
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32579413P2' xml:id='OTP32579413P2'><rs ref='#S32062514'>Special Order.<lb/>
No—14</rs>.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32579413P3' xml:id='OTP32579413P3'>The permission given from these Hd. Qrs—dated July 3<add place='above'><hi rend='underline'>d</hi></add> 1865, by Capt <rs ref='#S32062515'>J. N. Jack</rs>. <rs ref='#S49748'>Provost Marshal</rs> is hereby revoked. <rs ref='#S25024386'>C. B. Clark</rs> <rs ref='#S77229'>Chief of Police</rs> under that permission, will notify the parties forming the police patrols to discontinue the practice of patroling the roads &amp; Counties armed. All <rs ref='#S62954'>arrests</rs> must be made by the proper military or civil authorities
</p>

<p corresp='TTP32579413P4' xml:id='OTP32579413P4'><rs ref='#S32062516'>P. Jones Yorke</rs><lb/>
Lt Colonel Comdg— 
</p>


        </div>
  </body>
